//Cards //Atheon Atheon, Time Conflux
To speak of Atheon is to accept certain limitations. We are ill-equipped to understand an entity that defies simple causality. Let us accept these limitations and proceed.\nAtheon waits in the Vault of Glass. Just as Atheon sidesteps \'past\' and \'future\', it is impossible to say whether Atheon created the Vault or the Vault created Atheon. Causal pathways converge on Atheon from every axis in the space-time bulk.
